rComments: We had one assignment and quiz due every week that were very easy if you attended the lectures. The prof and TA were easily reachable if you needed help. I highly recommend this class not only because you'll get a good mark, but also because it was genuinely interesting.

She is a very nice professor. Assignments and quizzes are due every week but they are easy. She makes sure to have updated and relevant topics in her lectures which is awesome. I recommend her! Her TA's mark hard though so beware.

Professor Ferguson is the best!! I love her sooo much! Her lectures were so interesting and she would use real life examples for further detail. She was so caring and considerate and very accessible outside of classes :)) Im going to miss her a lot, I think If you have the chance you should take this class! I learnt so many life skills

Dr. Ferguson was a good teacher. Loved the simplicity of the content being taught. Weekly assignments were 2-4 pages long but don't take more than an hour or two to complete. TA's mark aggressively with no clear feedback. Midterm and final are fair; no surprises. Very interesting course, easy A, and would highly recommend.

Prof. Ferguson is the only instructor I've had that actually has fascinating anecdotes and oratory skills. Too bad her class was asynchronous for me, I'd love to meet her in person. Easy class but a lot of *easy* work. But, it was actually quite educational as I learned quite a bit. She knows how to teach!

Sherry is a very knowledgeable lady. She doesn't ask you trivial questions or trick questions on exams. She expects you to show her what you know, not her deceiving you with bogus questions on finals. Very well mannered individual with amazing personal anecdotes.

The content is quite easy, I took this as an easy A+ but the TA's were a lot harder than expected but overall its very possible to get a 10 with her. She's a very sweet lady, enjoyed her lectures. The only thing is there are weekly quizzes and activities which took a few hours every week to do, so easy A but heavy with assignments

Although rambles on a lot, Sherry is a great prof. overall. She makes everything clear and easy to understand. Although the textbook is not mandatory GET IT ANYWAY! Both the midterm and final exams had a few surprise questions that could only be found in the textbook.

Love Sherry with my whole heart! Her class is asynch which is nice since you can decide when you want to watch the lectures. Weekly lectures and chapter activities are easy and straightforward. Haven't done midterm yet but should be okay. Very nice and sweet, really knows her stuff, super organized. Offers optional live sessions with the TA!

The class is asynchronous and weekly chapter activities are worth 50% and the final is worth 50%. The activities are easy and for the final it was 120 MC in 130 minutes which wasn't too bad. The questions are all on one page and her lectures are all on Echo360. Speed up the lectures and occasionally use Google and Ctrl-F for an easy A.

Sherry is the BEST PROF EVER! She is so nice. Her course is regular you just have to put in the time and pat attention and you will be fine. When I had her she traded attendance with a platform so if you miss class she knows and you automatically loose participation points and they come in handy so attend! But you will love her and the TA :)

great class with a super sweet professor! chapter assignments each week were worth a total of 50%, and the rest was in a midterm and a final. rent the textbook, speed up the lectures and you'll be golden!

Class is asynchronous which is amazing. Take all your notes online and "command F" everything for the exam and midterm and you'll get 100%. I will be looking into taking any class with this prof again, she is the best!
She's honestly the best prof I've ever had. Is super sweet, caring, interesting, kind, and really wants you to succeed. She explains things clearly and is very experienced.

Prof. Ferguson is a gem! She's very sweet and patient, and she knows her material very well (she has written several textbooks including the one for this course). She tends to talk a lot as she has lots of examples, but they emphasize her point and they are always relevant to the material.

A SUPER NICE Prof at uOttawa. She cares about the students. She prerecorded her all lecture and can access at all time for the class. Her TAs are great and helpful. Also, be sure to READ the TEXTBOOK because it will be helpful for the midterm and final exams, and of course, activities.

Professor Ferguson is the sweetest and wisest professor I have come across to date. It is clear that she cares so deeply for her students, not only academically but personally as well. She may share many personal anecdotes, but those are specifically what help us remember important teachings in class. She is empathetic, kind, and an absolute joy.
AMAZING TEACHER! Best professor I have had!

AH-MAZING TEACHER! i can rave about her for hours, she is an absolute gem. She's a fast replier to emails and will admit if she made a mistake in her tests, and give extra marks to the entire class. Love her, i wish school wasn't online just so i can give her a hug in real life.
Sherry is an AMAZING professor, if you ever have a chance to take her class I recommend her! Her stories she tells are really good

Sherry Ferguson is an amazing prof! She is so respectful and caring towards her students. Her lectures are easy to understand and interesting. Exam material is not too difficult, just make sure you make use of the textbook. Shes also always open to getting to know her students and making us as comfortable with the course as possible. Great TAS!

Sherry did an awesome job with online teaching, her lectures were prerecorded and could be accessed at anytime. Her TAs are incredible and I enjoyed the class. Midterm and Exam were super easy and I feel like I actually learnt a lot from the class. TEXTBOOK IS USEFUL.
Sherry is a very sweet lady and makes her lectures very engaging and interesting with all of her little stories! Would definitely take one of her classes again!

Sherry is an absolute gem, especially Tristan!!! (the TA) discussion groups are the easiest way to get a realllly good mark. Lots of little activities every week, but midterms/final all multiple choice. Take good notes, speed up the lectures and it'll be your easiest course.
Solid class if you put some effort in should be an easy A. Prof is a sweetheart too

Very sweet, older lady. The 2 midterms and final are fairly easy and super straightforward. Participation is 20%, but her lectures are usually quite interactive (volunteers coming up to do psychological activities) so it doesn't feel like a pain in the a** to show up. All in all, I feel like I learnt a lot of interesting stuff from this class.
Easiest class Ive ever taken. Super clear expectations.

Attendance is 20% of the mark so show up. Midterms and final were pretty fair all thing she discusses in class are in the textbook. I only read what she calls the text boxes because thats what provided any additional information for the exam That and studying the lectures you should have no problem :)

Amazing prof! She explains the concepts well and she keeps you focused. Her PWPs can be dry but she gets you through it by telling interesting stories. If you pay attention, known the vocab you will do well.

Professor Sherry's class was really fun and the knowledge she taught was useful for the exam. The participation mark worth 20% which is a easy mark to get. The TA is super helpful and responsible as well.
Sherry is a really good prof, caring about students. The organized lectures and exmas are reasonable. If you make efforts, you will get a good mark!

Sherry is a nice old lady who's clearly had experience in the field of communication. Her intro course is easy as long as you show up to class, as participation counts for 20% of your mark. The tests are easy but very vocabulary-intensive. The textbook is definitely beneficial because all of the vocab can be found in it. Overall would take it again

Dr. Ferguson is very sweet and friendly but an abysmal instructor. She often recounts completely unrelated anecdotes and otherwise just reads off of her slides. Attendance counts for 20%. She assigned two textbooks (she wrote them both) and together they were over $200. Shes too focused on the professionalization of her students.

Sherry is honestly a fantastic prof. Attendance is graded so make sure you show up, lectures are very interesting and she does a great job of teaching you all the concepts and ideas. She's not so great with technology so there might be a couple delays in class. But overall an amazing prof and would definitely take again.

Overall good prof and good class, the only reason I showed up to the lectures was to get participation marks. She uses the textbook that she wrote for the class so everything she says in the lecture is directly quoted in the text. I watched Netlfix the whole time and got a good mark. Really sweet old lady.

Super nice prof, I would definitely take one of her classes again. Pretty easy midterms, just make sure you're listening in class. The textbook is unnecessary, seeing as her slides are practically the same information. And attendance is a solid portion of your grade, so make sure you show up.

Professor Ferguson is very well versed in communication and teaches the material clearly and consicely. She's also very kind and caring. Attendance is graded online so you have to show up. The only downside to this class is the reliance on technology, because she needs the TA to help her with the computer almost every class.
Very knowledgeable and well versed in the course content. Participation marks are easy and done online. Read the textbook, she covers it all anyways.
would ABSOLUTELY take again

Sherry is a good professor. I would take another class with her. Only downside--there are class exercises all of the time where your group must present the work after. Not worth any marks, it just gets really annoying. 1/2 of the class was group work, the other 1/2 was individual. No written tests. All assignments and take homes. Overall good prof
She was very clear and organized about the subject matter. Welcomed participation and seemed like a genuinely nice person.

Sherry was probably one of my favourite professors. She is the sweetest thing and always smiling which makes me look forward coming to her class. You must attend her class as she uses participation as part of your mark, discusses examples that will be on future exams as well as movies. Overall, a very enjoyable and easy class

She uses lecture tools so its easy to look back at old slides and ask questions in class. You get participation marks in class. She's interesting and up-to-date with her lectures. Tests are easy if you study the textbook, slides, and in-class videos! Would take her as a prof again!

Great prof! Course content was easy to understand. She and another prof at the school wrote the textbook it was well written, interesting, and easy to understand. The lectures were a repeat of what you read in the book but she made them interesting. Mini quizzes almost every class on lecture tools for participation marks. Would take her class again

Participation marks in every class. Lectures are boring and straight from the textbook with the exception of the occasional video. Tests are all multiple choice and very easy but make sure you read the textbook and text-boxes in it because she asks a lot of questions based on those. Generally quite a nice prof and an easy class.

She can't really use technology, and yeah she rambles on for quite a while, but if you show up to class and make sure to do the readings, the textbook and tests go hand in hand.  Although sometimes shes unclear about some concepts, shes overall a pretty decent teacher.  Not an especially difficult class. Participation was worth a lot.
I love her so much. She is an amazing woman! She's so easy to listen to, her lectures are interesting, and she makes the course fun and engaging. I would definitely take any of her classes again!

Amazing speaker, best professor I have had in a 200+ lecture hall. Tests are reasonable- if you study the lecture notes & go to the class, you will get higher than a B. (Textbook is necessary for a few questions on the exams) Interesting course. Would 100% take another course taught by Sherry. Lovely lady, you can tell she is sincere.

Great prof! Does a lot of activities in class to keep it interesting and uses lecture tools. The class is super easy, and 20 percent of your mark is simply participation. All of the tests are very fair and very easy. Would take another one of her classes for sure. :)

Professor Ferguson's class was interesting and very easy to follow. She also included various group work in class, which aided us in grasping the learned concepts. I would recommend taking her course.

Prof Ferguson is amazing. She's very clear in her lectures and her exams are super easy. She also does activities with the class to get us more involved which makes the class fun and much more interesting!

Horrible prof; gets the TA to do the majority of the work and spends about half the class figuring out technology. Any questions asked outside of class are redirected to the TA, and exams are extremely confusing (she words her questions with double negatives). Avoid her if possible.
no readings + no exams = best elective ever!
Very slow, fairly monotonous. Spent half the time trying to figure out the technology in the classroom. It got on my nerves that she mispronounced very basic words.
Ok class, a bit long, but not a big work load.  Nice to have a group project and not have to worry about a final or a paper
great prof

She is a very bad writer - you can't understand her comments.  She seems deaf/blind most of the time, and she is very slooooow.  She should not be teaching Public Speaking because she is monotonous and uninteresting.  Way too many examples.  BOOOOORING!!!  Retire immediately.
If you want a sweet, befuddled prof she's your woman.. If you want to learn something beyond a kindergarten level, go elsewhere!! Means well but needs some major overhaul of her classes.
Nice and caring person. She knows her stuff. She makes it easy for everyone to learn. Kind hearted.
Prof Ferguson is an excellent prof that really gets the student involved in the course. A+
Prof Ferguson knows her stuff, but she's clumsy.  She also needs to make her criteria a little harder so there's actually a goal to be met.
Excellent material & prof. Very practical for real world. Concerned about your image & ability to persuade?  Take this course!
Useless course. Useless Prof.
I did not learn a thing in this class.
tried to be to nice! Phony!
Stimulating and interresting.
EXCELLENT teacher. She's the best! You can't help but love her.
loads of speechwriting experience and it comes through. good class.
She actually cares about her students. A very sweet prof.
The sweetest professor
